            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10663",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mattsidesinger",
                        "name": "mattsidesinger",
                        "displayName": "Matt Sidesinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "1. Using version 0.15, I am unable to repeat the \"sort\" parameter issue.  I could not find any reference to any variables named \"SearchIndex\" ($SearchIndex).\n\n2.  I agree, the list of valid sort values in $_searchSort should be language dependent.  I'll try to work on a solution to this problem.\n\nHere is just the difference between the US and DE sort values for the 'Books' category.\nhttp:\/\/docs.amazonwebservices.com\/AWSEcommerceService\/2006-06-28\/ApiReference\/USSortValuesArticle.html#books\nhttp:\/\/docs.amazonwebservices.com\/AWSEcommerceService\/2006-06-28\/ApiReference\/DESortValuesArticle.html#books\n\n3. In 0.15 there still is no reference to the $_sortVerbs array.",
